553
00:32:29.116 --> 00:32:31.076
So osteosarcoma is a primary bone tumor.

554
00:32:31.096 --> 00:32:33.616
There are about 600 cases per year in the United States.

555
00:32:34.516 --> 00:32:38.136
It most often occurs around the knees, and 40% of

556
00:32:38.216 --> 00:32:41.365
patients will have advanced disease, with about half of those having advanced

557
00:32:41.416 --> 00:32:44.916
disease at diagnosis and half having advanced disease at the time

558
00:32:45.036 --> 00:32:47.916
of relapse after completing frontline therapy.

559
00:32:49.026 --> 00:32:52.056
The most common site of metastatic disease is the lung.

560
00:32:52.096 --> 00:32:55.996
Following standard chemotherapy treatment with doxorubicin, cisplatin, and

561
00:32:56.036 --> 00:32:59.896
high-dose methotrexate, the 10-year overall survival if you

562
00:33:00.036 --> 00:33:03.205
have advanced disease at diagnosis is only 25%.

563
00:33:03.786 --> 00:33:07.116
If you have localized disease, that long-term overall survival is

564
00:33:07.316 --> 00:33:08.066
75%.

565
00:33:08.876 --> 00:33:12.116
But in osteosarcoma, our ability to predict

566
00:33:13.096 --> 00:33:15.516
whether you'll survive your metastatic disease or

567
00:33:16.336 --> 00:33:19.276
will relapse after localized disease is quite poor.

568
00:33:20.356 --> 00:33:24.236
For prognostic factors, we use poor histologic response, which

569
00:33:24.296 --> 00:33:27.536
is looking at how many cells are dead after 10 weeks of initial

570
00:33:27.616 --> 00:33:31.396
chemotherapy, and the location of the tumor, and whether or not there's advanced

571
00:33:31.436 --> 00:33:35.216
disease at diagnosis. These, to me, are really observations

572
00:33:35.226 --> 00:33:38.656
of bad behavior rather than a true

573
00:33:38.696 --> 00:33:41.156
understanding of the underlying biology.

574
00:33:42.106 --> 00:33:45.736
And then I'll just mention that for osteosarcoma and Ewing sarcoma, the other bone

575
00:33:45.816 --> 00:33:49.376
sarcoma I'll discuss, there's a very high burden of both

576
00:33:49.436 --> 00:33:52.856
acute and late toxicity and also a high treatment burden.

577
00:33:52.916 --> 00:33:56.636
This chemotherapy and the chemotherapy we use for Ewing sarcoma

578
00:33:56.896 --> 00:34:00.756
is very intense and really removes people from their day-to-day lives.

579
00:34:01.576 --> 00:34:05.216
And finally, in osteosarcoma, there's been no improvement in outcomes in 40

580
00:34:05.316 --> 00:34:05.656
years.

581
00:34:06.856 --> 00:34:10.676
And I'm showing you that in the survival curves above, which

582
00:34:10.736 --> 00:34:13.897
are by decade and are population data from the United States.

583
00:34:14.957 --> 00:34:18.245
That's because chemotherapy intensification, immune checkpoint inhibitors, and

584
00:34:18.296 --> 00:34:21.615
molecularly targeted therapy are ineffective in this disease.

585
00:34:22.397 --> 00:34:25.917
That's in contrast to neuroblastoma, which is shown on the right and has had

586
00:34:25.957 --> 00:34:27.816
successive improvements in outcomes.

587
00:34:28.836 --> 00:34:32.397
In part, in neuroblastoma, that's due to the ability to recognize

588
00:34:32.476 --> 00:34:36.397
distinct disease subgroups, which are defined both by clinical

