593
00:34:52.596 --> 00:34:56.357
by addressing a molecular target that you find in those

594
00:34:56.397 --> 00:34:57.876
high-risk patient populations.

595
00:34:59.756 --> 00:35:03.696
In osteosarcoma, while we've known about the molecular features for

596
00:35:03.736 --> 00:35:07.676
quite some time, our lack of progress is in part due to the failure to

597
00:35:07.716 --> 00:35:09.536
identify these biologic subgroups.

598
00:35:10.116 --> 00:35:13.636
So osteosarcoma, as shown in the karyotype at the top and the circus plot below,

599
00:35:13.756 --> 00:35:15.376
has a highly complex genome

600
00:35:16.336 --> 00:35:17.696
characterized by chromothripsis.

601
00:35:17.756 --> 00:35:21.476
It's the cancer type with the heaviest burden or the largest percentage of

602
00:35:21.536 --> 00:35:23.556
cases impacted by chromothripsis.

603
00:35:24.256 --> 00:35:28.136
That leads to universal inactivation of TP53, most often through

